This page is for picture guides assembled by community members. 

''Note that you are encouraged to read the [[KVM|official KVM guide]] and documentation first and only refer here if are still unsure about what to do. Please report any uncertainties about the official guide on the [https://www.whonix.org/forum/index.php/board,15.0.html KVM support forum].''

<pre>
sudo apt-get update
</pre>
[[File:1.jpg|400px]]
<pre>
sudo apt-get install qemu-kvm libvirt-bin virt-manager
</pre>
[[File:2.jpg|400px]]
<pre>
sudo ln -s /etc/apparmor.d/libvirt/TEMPLATE.qemu /etc/apparmor.d/libvirt/TEMPLATE.kvm
</pre>
[[File:3.jpg|400px]]
<pre>
sudo addgroup "$(whoami)" libvirt
</pre>
[[File:4.jpg|400px]]
<pre>
sudo addgroup "$(whoami)" kvm
</pre>
[[File:5.jpg|400px]]
<pre>
sudo reboot
</pre>
[[File:6.jpg|400px]]
<pre>
virsh -c qemu:///system net-autostart default
</pre>
<pre>
virsh -c qemu:///system net-start default
</pre>
[[File:7.jpg|400px]]

To get the qcow2 images please open the latest version numbered folder you see in this link and download the files ending in *'''libvirt.xz''':
http://mirror.whonix.de/

[[File:8.jpg|400px]]
<pre>
tar -xvf ~/Whonix-Gateway-*.libvirt.xz
</pre>
<pre>
tar -xvf ~/Whonix-Workstation-*.libvirt.xz
</pre>
[[File:9.jpg|400px]]

[[File:10.jpg|400px]]
<pre>
virsh -c qemu:///system define Whonix-Gateway*.xml
</pre>
<pre>
virsh -c qemu:///system net-define Whonix_network*.xml
</pre>
<pre>
virsh -c qemu:///system net-autostart Whonix
</pre>
<pre>
virsh -c qemu:///system net-start Whonix
</pre>
<pre>
virsh -c qemu:///system define Whonix-Workstation*.xml
</pre>
[[File:11.jpg|400px]]
<pre>
sudo mv Whonix-Gateway*.qcow2 /var/lib/libvirt/images/Whonix-Gateway.qcow2
</pre>
<pre>
sudo mv Whonix-Workstation*.qcow2 /var/lib/libvirt/images/Whonix-Workstation.qcow2
</pre>
